    excerpt: "Scientists analyzed 57 studies of coral reefs worldwide to test whether remote reefs far from human populations are more resilient to climate disturbances like bleaching and storms. Surprisingly, they found that isolation from humans doesn't make coral reefs more resilient, and some reefs near large human populations actually recovered faster from disturbances.",
