    excerpt: "Scientists developed a new framework to identify 'tipping points' in the California Current marine ecosystem - critical thresholds where small changes in environmental conditions or human activities can trigger large, sudden shifts in marine life. They found evidence that five different aspects of the ecosystem may respond dramatically to changes in the Pacific Decadal Oscillation.",
